Detailed ASCII Layout Mockup - Restrained Two-Column CV with Photo

Use this wireframe as the structural blueprint for a restrained two-column CV with photo. This layout is an allowed exception to the single-column default and must remain disciplined, light, and formal rather than looking like a dark-sidebar resume template.

## Page Format

```text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ PAGE FORMAT                                                                                  │
│ A4 PORTRAIT                                                                                  │
│ Top margin: 16 mm   Bottom margin: 16 mm   Left margin: 18 mm   Right margin: 18 mm        │
│ Layout: RESTRAINED TWO-COLUMN                                                                │
│ Left column width: 28% to 32%                                                                │
│ Right column width: 68% to 72%                                                               │
│ Gutter: 6 mm to 8 mm                                                                         │
│ Sidebar treatment: white or barely tinted neutral only if necessary                          │
│ Photo treatment: rectangular, top-right, around 32 mm wide                                  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Core layout rules:

* Left column stays narrow and utility-focused.
* Right column remains visually dominant.
* Do not use a dark sidebar block.
* Sidebar background must remain white or a barely tinted neutral only if necessary.
* Do not add cards, boxed widgets, rating bars, or decorative fills just because a second column exists.
* The photo supports the brand impression and must not dominate the page.

## Column Roles

Use this allocation by default:

* Left column: contact, key skills, languages, certifications, tools
* Right column: summary, experience, education, achievements

The left column is support material. The right column carries the main reading flow and should clearly dominate the page.

## Header Band With Photo

```text
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [NAME BLOCK - LEFT]                                            [PHOTO BLOCK - RIGHT]        │
│                                                                                              │
│ FULL NAME                                                             ┌──────────────────┐    │
│ Professional Title / Positioning Line                                 │                  │    │
│ City, Country · Phone · Email · LinkedIn · Website                    │   RECTANGULAR    │    │
│                                                                       │     HEADSHOT      │    │
│                                                                       │                  │    │
│                                                                       └──────────────────┘    │
│                                                                                              │
│ Optional thin divider rule spanning full usable width below header                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Header rules:

* Keep the text block left aligned.
* Keep the photo in the same top band as the name block.
* Place the photo top right.
* Use a rectangular portrait crop showing head and upper shoulders.
* Keep the photo width around 32 mm.
* Avoid circular crops, filters, shadows, thick borders, and decorative frames.
* Do not let the photo drop so low that it disrupts the summary start.

Suggested header rhythm:

* 8-12 pt from top margin to name
* 4-6 pt from name to title
* 4-6 pt from title to contact line
* 10-14 pt from contact line to divider rule
* 14-18 pt from divider rule to the start of the two-column body

