## Construction Spec

### 1. Header Block

```text
FULL NAME
Professional Title / Positioning Line
City, Country · Phone · Email · LinkedIn · Website
```

Photo block:

```text
┌──────────────────┐
│                  │
│   HEADSHOT       │
│   RECTANGULAR    │
│                  │
└──────────────────┘
```

Rules:

* Name is the largest element on the page.
* Title sits directly below the name.
* Contact line reads as compact metadata rather than body copy.
* Keep the text header left aligned and the photo top right in the same band.
* Maintain a clear breathing gap between the text block and the photo block.

### 2. Left Column

Preferred section order:

```text
CONTACT
CORE SKILLS
LANGUAGES
CERTIFICATIONS
TOOLS
```

Rules:

* Keep entries concise and vertically compact.
* Use text lists, not visual widgets.
* Avoid large gaps between small sections.
* If the sidebar receives a tint, it must be a barely visible neutral only.
* The left column must never dominate the right column visually.

Example patterns:

```text
CONTACT
Berlin, Germany
+49 000 000 000
name@email.com
linkedin.com/in/name
website.com
```

```text
CORE SKILLS
Business Development
Commercial Strategy
Stakeholder Management
Negotiation
CRM Management
Forecasting
```

```text
LANGUAGES
English - Native
German - Professional
Swedish - Conversational
```

### 3. Right Column

Preferred section order:

```text
PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE
EDUCATION
ADDITIONAL INFORMATION
```

Rules:

* Summary starts at the top of the right column.
* Experience is the dominant block in the layout.
* Education is concise and placed below experience unless early-career content demands otherwise.
* Additional information remains short and secondary.

### 4. Professional Summary

```text
PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
Short paragraph of 3-5 lines with concise executive positioning.
```

Rules:

* Keep it one compact paragraph.
* Do not fragment it into multiple mini-lines.
* Avoid first-person voice and generic self-description.

### 5. Professional Experience

```text
ROLE TITLE                                            MMM YYYY - MMM YYYY
Company Name, Location
Optional one-line descriptor if context is needed
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
• Action + scope/context + measurable result
```

Rules:

* Role title and date share one line.
* Date stays flush right across every role.
* Company line sits below role title.
* Bullets use a consistent hanging indent.
* Space between roles is larger than space between bullets.

### 6. Education

```text
EDUCATION
Degree / Qualification                               YYYY - YYYY
Institution, Location
Optional honors / notable module if relevant
```

Rules:

* Keep entries concise.
* Align dates consistently with experience entries.
* Sort newest first.

### 7. Additional Left-Column Sections

Certifications:

```text
CERTIFICATIONS
Certification Name - Issuer - Year
Certification Name - Issuer - Year
```

Tools:

```text
TOOLS
Salesforce
HubSpot
Excel
Power BI
Microsoft 365
```

Rules:

* Use plain text lines only.
* No icons, bars, dots, stars, or proficiency meters.
* Keep labels short enough to avoid awkward wrapping in the narrow column.

## Spacing And Alignment

Vertical rhythm:

```text
[Top margin]
Header content
small gap
Divider rule
medium gap
Two-column body starts
small gap between heading and content
medium gap between sections
...
[Bottom margin]
```

Suggested spacing:

* 4-8 pt between heading and section content
* 10-14 pt between small left-column sections
* 12-16 pt between major right-column sections
* 10-14 pt between experience entries
* 2-4 pt between bullets inside a role

Alignment system:

```text
LEFT EDGE OF HEADER TEXT
RIGHT EDGE OF PHOTO
LEFT EDGE OF LEFT COLUMN CONTENT
LEFT EDGE OF RIGHT COLUMN CONTENT
RIGHT EDGE OF DATE COLUMN
RIGHT EDGE OF PAGE CONTENT FIELD
```

Rules:

* Respect the 6 mm to 8 mm gutter consistently.
* Do not let left-column sections drift horizontally.
* Do not create separate floating alignment systems inside the same column.
* Dates in the right column must align consistently.

## Page-Break Logic

If the CV flows to page 2:

* Do not repeat the photo on page 2.
* Repeat a small name + contact header only if needed.
* Continue the same two-column grid only if both columns still carry meaningful content.
* If the remaining content is mostly experience, it is acceptable for page 2 to collapse to a cleaner single-column continuation.

Continuation concept:

```text
PAGE 2 START
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ FULL NAME  ·  Email  ·  Phone                                                                │
│ ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │
│                                                                                              │
│ PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE (continued if necessary)                                             │
│ ROLE TITLE                                            MMM YYYY - MMM YYYY                    │
│ Company Name, Location                                                                        │
│ • Bullet                                                                                     │
│ • Bullet                                                                                     │
│                                                                                              │
│ EDUCATION                                                                                    │
│ ...                                                                                          │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Rules:

* Do not split a heading from its content at a page break.
* Do not leave a single orphan bullet on page 2 if it can be avoided.
* Do not force an empty-looking left column on page 2 if the content no longer supports it.

## Micro-Detail Checklist

* Left column width stays between 28% and 32%.
* Right column width stays between 68% and 72%.
* Gutter stays between 6 mm and 8 mm.
* Left column remains narrow and supportive.
* Right column clearly dominates the reading flow.
* No dark sidebar block appears anywhere.
* Sidebar background remains white or barely tinted neutral only if necessary.
* Photo is rectangular, top right, and around 32 mm wide.
* Photo stays inside the header band only.
* Photo supports the page and does not dominate it.
* No colored cards, rating bars, decorative shapes, or boxed widgets appear in the sidebar.
* Header remains clean and left aligned.
* Summary reads as one compact paragraph.
* Experience remains the primary block.
* Dates align consistently.
* The layout feels formal, premium, and restrained rather than trendy.
